      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments used porcine blood at 37°C, hematocrit 33±2%, with flow rates measured by Coriolis meter (±0.5%). CFD boundary conditions were set to match measured mean values. Temperature sensitivity was assessed via a ±2°C parametric sweep with negligible effect on RHI (<1%)."
